summary: An ordinance accepting deeds from Benjamin B. Putnam and Lucy H. Putnam, husband and wife, to the City of Seattle, executed on the 24th day of March, 1923; and August Wilen and Erika L. Wilen, husband and wife, to the City of Seattle, executed on the 15th day of June, 1923, and laying off 2nd Avenue Northwest and West 57th Street.
